<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1445,1974]" lastBlockId="5.[159,1421,204,463]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1841,1866]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[346,497,1841,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quito">
<emphasis box="[346,497,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Agrilus quito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a group characterized by the pronotum being blue-green, by median pubescence of elytra Y-shaped or inverted “T”, and rounded elytral apex. In this group, in size and shape, the species most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[420,510,1914,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quito">
<emphasis box="[420,510,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">A. quito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName authority="Curletti &amp; Brule, 2011" authorityName="Curletti &amp; Brule" authorityYear="2011" box="[546,935,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perditus">
<emphasis box="[546,670,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">A. perditus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Curletti" box="[678,935,1913,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" refString="Curletti, G. &amp; Brule, S. (2011) Agrilus, Agriloides et Autarcontes de Guyane. Magellanes ed. Ex Natura, 2, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2011">
Curletti &amp; Brûlé, 
<number box="[880,935,1914,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus box="[951,1001,1914,1938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">type</typeStatus>
in MCCI- from French 
<collectingCountry box="[1278,1369,1914,1938]" name="Guyana" pageId="4" pageNumber="579">Guyana</collectingCountry>
. Both have the head with a red vertex, and a green pronotum, but they differ in the following main characters: 
<emphasis box="[159,913,204,225]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">
<taxonomicName box="[159,239,204,225]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quito">A. quito</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[804,913,204,225]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perditus">A. perditus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[159,1421,204,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">- Dorsal color more brilliant. - Dorsal color darker and less bright. - Sculpture of vertex with strong longitudinal stripes. - Sculpture of vertex punctiform. - Pronotum wider on posterior half, strongly sinuate before the - Pronotum wider on anterior half with posterior angles more basal angles that are more acute. squared.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[159,1421,204,463]" box="[159,1080,400,422]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">- Elytral pubescence yellow. - Elytral pubescence white.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[159,1421,204,463]" box="[159,1118,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">
- Metatarsal formula 
<number box="[373,382,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="1.0">1</number>
&lt;
<number box="[399,414,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[430,443,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="3.0">3</number>
. - Metatarsal formula 
<number box="[1017,1026,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="1.0">1</number>
= 
<number box="[1042,1056,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1072,1084,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number box="[1100,1114,441,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" value="4.0">4</number>
.
</paragraph>
